[thinking] **Considering serialization options**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about the serialization process after readObject. It seems like it might be better not to detach the parent to ensure that top scope serialization works. But I wonder if the size will be enormous — maybe the serialize package can handle that, even if I test under 60. I could also consider using ScriptableOutputStream, but there’s the issue with NativeJavaObject’s private writeObject and its handling of Java serialization. Inspecting upstream tests could be necessary too.
